-- в”Ђв”Ђ Respond.io в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Respond.io is an AI-powered business messaging platform that unifies WhatsApp, Messenger, Instagram, Telegram, and other channels into one inbox for sales and support teams.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Tiered monthly or annual subscription based on users and monthly active contacts$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$$79/month billed annually (Starter), or $99/month billed monthly$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2017, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Approximately 196 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Respond.io Review 2026: Pricing, Features and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Respond.io unifies WhatsApp, Messenger, Instagram and more into one AI-powered inbox. Compare 2026 pricing plans, features, pros/cons and FAQs.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Respond.io is a business messaging and customer conversation management platform founded in 2017 and headquartered in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, with a team of roughly 196 people as of 2026. The company has raised a total of about $71.3 million, including a $7 million Series A led by Headline and a $62.5 million Series B led by Camber Partners announced in June 2026 that it said would fund expansion into North America and Europe and support acquisitions. The product's core value proposition is unifying messaging channels, including the WhatsApp Business API, Facebook Messenger, Instagram DMs, Telegram, WeChat, LINE, Viber, SMS, email, and web chat, into a single shared inbox so sales, marketing, and support teams can manage every customer conversation from one place, with routing rules, team collision-avoidance, and reporting layered on top. Respond.io has increasingly positioned itself around AI: its AI Agents feature lets teams deploy AI-driven auto-responders and lead-qualification bots directly inside conversations, and AI Prompts and AI Assist features help human agents draft replies faster. Pricing is based on a combination of user seats and Monthly Active Contacts, or MACs, which are unique contacts a business messages within a billing period. As of 2026 there are four tiers: Starter at $79/month billed annually, or $99/month billed monthly, includes 5 users and unlimited MACs but excludes broadcasts, workflow automation, and AI Agents; Growth at $159/month billed annually, or $199/month billed monthly, includes 10 users, starts with 1,000 MACs, and unlocks broadcasts, workflow automation, AI Agents, Zapier and Make integrations, and a developer API, with overage billed at $12 per additional 100 MACs; Advanced at $279/month billed annually, or $349/month billed monthly, includes 10 users, adds SSO, Salesforce integration, multiple workspaces, and webhook or HTTP-request steps in workflows, with overage at $15 per 100 MACs; and Enterprise is custom-priced with unlimited users, higher API limits, and a dedicated success manager. All self-serve plans include a 7-day free trial with Growth-level features. Underlying Meta and WhatsApp messaging fees are billed separately by Meta on top of respond.io's own subscription. The platform is widely used by e-commerce brands, real estate agencies, and B2B sales teams in markets with high WhatsApp usage, such as Southeast Asia, Latin America, and the Middle East, that need to manage high message volumes without losing conversations across channels.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '5ba6eb3b-9e95-46c8-907b-8f15ea5b72ae';

